    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-03-09T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-03-09T17:00:00-05:00" n="471"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d471">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 656.119/202</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PWH1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-03-09T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 9, 1918, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6826. For <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SLP1">Sheldon</persName> from
                    War Trade Board.</p>
                <p>No. 184. Embassy’s 8917, March 6, 7 p.m. Your 235. <hi rend="italic"
                        >Wieldrecht</hi> is now New York Harbor. The names of the nine Dutch boats
                    and destinations are as follows: <hi rend="italic">Randwyk, Pollux,
                        Winterswyk</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Clio</hi> to Key West; <hi
                        rend="italic">Jan van Nassau, Beukelsdyk</hi>, and <hi rend="italic"
                        >Zuiderdyk</hi> to San Juan; <hi rend="italic">Cornelis</hi> and <hi
                        rend="italic">Java</hi> to Panama Canal.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PFL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
